UPDATE: The House PASSED the First Responders Passport Act.
We had a great Tele-Town Hall tonight. Thank you to everyone who participated and added to the discussion. pic.twitter.com/djM9otaQvL

The First Responders Passport Act:

✅ Strengthens existing passport fee exemptions for state/locally employed first responders contracted with the US Gov to deploy abroad

✅ Extends exemption to volunteer first responders, who play a critical role on disaster response teams

The First Responders Passport Act, gives the Secretary of State discretion to waive passport fees for first responders contracted to help the US Government respond to natural disasters abroad, like Hurricane Dorian.
